n%20would%20likely%20also%20affect%20Trump's%20status%20for%20the%20Nov.%205%20general%20election.%20Nonpartisan%20U.S.%20election%20forecasters%20view%20Colorado%20as%20safely%20Democratic%2C%20meaning%20that%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20will%20likely%20carry%20the%20state%20regardless%20of%20Trump's%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20brought%20by%20a%20group%20of%20Colorado%20voters%2C%20aided%20by%20the%20group%20Citizens%20for%20Responsibility%20and%20Ethics%20in%20Washington%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20Trump%20should%20be%20disqualified%20for%20inciting%20his%20supporters%20to%20attack%20the%20Capitol%20in%20a%20failed%20attempt%20to%20obstruct%20the%20transfer%20of%20presidential%20power%20to%20Biden%20after%20the%202020%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20campaign%20called%20the%20court%20decision%20%26quot%3Bflawed%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bundemocratic%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20would%20be%20appealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20issued%20a%20completely%20flawed%20decision%20tonight%20and%20we%20will%20swiftly%20file%20an%20appeal%20to%20the%20United%20States%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20a%20concurrent%20request%20for%20a%20stay%20of%20this%20deeply%20undemocratic%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20Trump%20campaign%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20campaign%20has%20condemned%2014th%20Amendment%20challenges%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20deny%20millions%20of%20voters%20their%20preferred%20choice%20for%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20is%20a%20victory%20for%20advocacy%20groups%20and%20anti-Trump%20voters%20who%20have%20mounted%20several%20similar%20legal%20challenges%20to%20Trump's%20candidacy%20under%20section%203%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%2C%20which%20was%20enacted%20after%20the%20Civil%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20reverses%20a%20ruling%20by%20a%20lower%20court%20judge%20who%20found%20Trump%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%20by%20inciting%20his%20supporters%20to%20violence%2C%20but%2C%20as%20president%2C%20Trump%20was%20not%20an%20%26quot%3Bofficer%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20who%20could%20be%20disqualified%20under%20the%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20for%20Trump%20argued%20that%20the%20riot%20at%20the%20Capitol%20was%20not%20serious%20enough%20to%20qualify%20as%20an%20insurrection%20and%20that%20Trump's%20remarks%20to%20his%20supporters%20in%20Washington%20that%20day%20were%20protected%20by%20his%20right%20to%20free%20speech.%20The%20lawyer%20contended%20that%20courts%20do%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20order%20Trump%20removed%20from%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20have%20hoped%20to%20use%20the%20case%20to%20boost%20a%20wider%20disqualification%20effort%20and%20potentially%20put%20the%20issue%20before%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court's%206-3%20conservative%20majority%20includes%20three%20Trump%20appointees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20court%20said%20the%20ruling%20is%20stayed%20until%20Jan.%204%2C%202024%2C%20to%20allow%20for%20appeals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20court's%20decision%20today%20affirms%20what%20our%20clients%20alleged%20in%20this%20lawsuit%3A%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20an%20insurrectionist%20who%20disqualified%20himself%20from%20office%20under%20Section%203%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20based%20on%20his%20role%20in%20the%20January%206th%20attack%20on%20the%20Capitol%2C%20and%20that%20Secretary%20Griswold%20must%20keep%20him%20off%20of%20Colorado's%20primary%20ballot.%20It%20is%20not%20only%20historic%20and%20justified%2C%20but%20is%20necessary%20to%20protect%20the%20future%20of%20democracy%20in%20our%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20CREW%20President%20Noah%20Bookbinder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pu