made%20fighter%20jets%2C%20Tehran%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.irna.ir%2Fnews%2F85306643%2FReport-dubs-Iran-Russia-arms-deal-a-win-win%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%20that%20it%20is%20set%20to%20receive%20Su-35s%20in%20its%20first%20acquisition%20of%20foreign%20fighter%20jets%20in%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20fighters%2C%20along%20with%20the%20training%20jets%20and%20attack%20helicopters%20said%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20deal%2C%20would%20be%20a%20significant%20upgrade%20for%20Iran's%20air%20force%2C%20which%20fields%20an%20aging%20fleet%20of%20aircraft%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-destroyed-old-f14-tomcats-so-iran-couldnt-use-them-2020-8%5C%22%3EUS-made%20F-14s%3C%2Fa%3E%20acquired%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20deal%20falls%20through%2C%20some%20analysts%20believe%20Iran's%20current%20air%20force%20shouldn't%20be%20dismissed%20because%20of%20its%20advanced%20age.%20An%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplus.shephardmedia.com%2Fanalysis%2Fdecisive-edge-iranian-air-power-1980s-relic-or-cause-for-concern%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20published%20by%20Shephard%20Media%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%20that%20while%20Iranian's%20fighter%20fleet%20may%20face%20a%20distinct%20disadvantage%20against%20modern%20fighters%2C%20it%20could%20still%20challenge%20a%20local%20rival%2C%20largely%20because%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20fighting%20over%20home%20turf%20and%20with%20support%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20Iran's%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIranian%20aircrews%20also%20have%20more%20experience%20their%20their%20counterparts%20in%20Arab%20Gulf%20militaries%2C%20and%20Iran's%20anti-ship%20and%20air-defense%20missiles%20could%20take%20a%20toll%20during%20a%20clash%20in%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Shephard%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20F-4%20fighter%20jet%20underground%20base%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e411ed96242f0019e80c09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20military%20officials%20at%20an%20underground%20air%20force%20base%20in%20February.%3Cp%3EIranian%20Army%2FHandout%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20Bohl%2C%20a%20senior%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20analyst%20at%20the%20risk-intelligence%20company%20RANE%2C%20said%20Iran%20could%20probably%20have%20home-field%20advantages%20against%20an%20otherwise%20superior%20force%20depending%20on%20the%20circumstances%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bscale%20and%20scenario%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20hypothetical%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20surgical%20stealth%20strike%20might%20readily%20overcome%20Iran's%20air%20defenses%2C%20but%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20full-scale%20conventional%20war%2C%20Iran's%20air%20defenses%20combined%20with%20its%20aging%20air%20fleet%20might%20be%20able%20to%20score%20a%20handful%20of%20combat%20successes%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohl%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohl%20pointed%20to%20Serbia%20in%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20when%20its%20small%2C%20outdated%20air%20force%20faced%20NATO%20air%20forces%20and%20%26quot%3Bmanaged%20to%20still%20down%20a%20handful%20of%20American%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ff22-f117-rumors-about-how-china-got-j20-stealth-tech-2023-5%5C%22%3Ean%20F-117%20stealth%20jet%3C%2Fa%3E%20shot%20down%20by%20an%20anti-aircraft%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebastien%20Roblin%2C%20a%20widely%20published%20military-aviation%20journalist%2C%20noted%20that%20many%20of%20Iran's%20outdated%20fighters%20%E2%80%94%20including%20US-made%20F-4s%20and%20Soviet-designed%20MiG-29As%20%E2%80%94%20were%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20in%20their%20day%26quot%3B%20and%20have%20been%20kept%20flying%20through%20cannibalizing%20parts%2C%20reverse-engineering%2C%20and%20indigenously-developed%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20upgrades%20may%20be%20janky%2C%20but%20arguably%20it's%20prudent%20to%20assume%20they%20do%20the%20basic%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Iran's%20air%20force%20is%20otherwise%20outdated%20and%20would%20%26quot%3Bstruggle%20to%20achieve%20much%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20%26quot%3Bworld-class%26quot%3B%20US%20and%20Israeli%20air%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUkraine-style%20air%20denial%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20smoking%20debris%20of%20a%20Russian%20fighter%20jet%20that%20crashed%20in%20a%20field%20in%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6302a09fc9a2da001808f827%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22674%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20Su-35%20downed%20by%20Ukrainian%20forces%20in%20the%20Kharkiv%20region%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3EPress%20service%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%20General%20Staff%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Russia%20attacked%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20its%20larger%20and%20more%20modern%20air%20force%20was%20expected%20to%20overwhelm%20and%20destroy%20Ukrainian%20fighters%20and%20air%20defenses%2C%20but%20Ukraine's%20air%20force%20has%20survived%20and%20been%20able%20to%20deny%20Russia%20air%20superiority%20thanks%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-targeting-cant-catch-ukraine-air-force-top-us-general-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecombination%20of%20Russian%20missteps%20and%20its%20own%20ingenuity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoblin%20said%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20shows%20how%20an%20%26quot%3Boutdated%20air%20force%20sometimes%20can%20endure%20and%20impose%20costs%26quot%3B%20against%20a%20far%20more%20powerful%20adversary%20through%20%26quot%3Bsmart%20leverage%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20%26quot%3Bplanes'%20strengths%20without%20sacrificing%20them%20rashly%20and%20working%20the%20home%20field%20defensive%20advantage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIran%2C%20like%20Ukraine%2C%20has%20a%20%3Cem%3Elot%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%20and%20radar%2C%20which%2C%20if%20adroitly%20managed%2C%20can%20fence%20away%20hostile%20air-superiority%20jets%20and%20improve%20the%20survivability%20of%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20said.%20But%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20are%20much%20better%20than%20Russia%20at%20leveraging%20air%20power%2C%20using%20long-range%20reconnaissance%20and%20strikes%2C%20stealth%20aircraft%2C%20and%20advanced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-air-force-lacks-jets-to-destroy-ukraines-air-defenses-2023-11%5C%22%3Esuppression-of-enemy-air-defense%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoblin%20said%20that%20in%20air-to-air%20operations%2C%20Iranian%20pilots%20would%20likely%20face%20problems%20similar%20to%20those%20of%20%26quot%3BUkrainian%20pilots%20who%20find%20they%20can't%20press%20home%20attacks%20due%20to%20being%20outranged%20by%20enemy%20fire-and-forget%20beyond-visual-range%20missiles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20I'd%20guess%20American%20and%20Israeli%20pilots%20may%20more%20aggressively%20close%20with%20enemy%20air%20assets%20than%20Russian%20ones%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESu-35%20%E2%80%94%20no%20game-changer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20F-5%20fighter%20jet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581abe4a79e5746976ade5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Iranian%20F-5%20fighter%20jet%20lands%20in%20Chabahar%20city%20in%20June%202009.%3Cp%3EEBRAHIM%20NOROUZI%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBohl%20and%20Roblin%20both%20expect%20the%20eventual%20delivery%20of%20Su-35s%20to%20have%20limited%20impact%20on%20Iran's%20overall%20airpower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohl%20said%20the%20jets%20%26quot%3Bwould%20ease%20some%20of%20Iran's%20defense%20problems%20by%20providing%20it%20with%20at%20least%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20advanced%20aircraft%20that%20might%20be%20helpful%20in%20deterring%20a%20limited%20air%20campaign.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehran%20may%20treat%20the%20jets%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20like%20prestige%20prize%26quot%3B%20and%20be%20reluctant%20to%20use%20them%2C%20in%20which%20case%20they%20may%20be%20%26quot%3Bmore%20of%20a%20diplomatic%20and%20political%20win%20rather%20than%20a%20defense%20breakthrough%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohl%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIran%20may%20also%20try%20to%20use%20its%20Su-35s%20%26quot%3Bcautiously%20as%20a%20backfield%20airborne%20early-warning%20plane%2C%20much%20like%20it%20used%20the%20F-14's%20AWG-9%20radar%20during%20the%20Iran-Iraq%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Shephard%20analysis%20notes%20that%20in%20a%20conflict%20with%20local%20rivals%2C%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Iran's%20aircraft%20and%20aircrews%2C%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fonline-analysis%2Fmilitary-balance%2F2023%2F11%2Ffar-from-museum-pieces-iranian-missile-munition-and-uav-ambition-on-display%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eair-defense%20and%20land-attack%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20proximity%20of%20the%20combat%20zones%2C%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20bring%20its%20navy%20to%20bear%20may%20benefit%20Iranian%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20missile%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581ad681c5c7b8c9a099f4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIslamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20personnel%20next%20to%20a%20Majid%20anti-aircraft%20missile%20system%20during%20a%20rally%20in%20Tehran%20in%20November.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20better-armed%20and%20better-trained%20US%20and%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20however%2C%20Iran%20would%20face%20myriad%20disadvantages%20even%20%3Cem%3Eif%20it%20had%3C%2Fem%3E%20Su-35s.%20The%20US%20and%20Israeli%20air%20forces%20have%20extensive%20advantages%20in%20training%20and%20support%20assets%2C%20Roblin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Su-35's%20Irbis-E%20radar%20isn't%20a%20stealthy%20active%20electronically%20scanned%20array%20radar%20like%20those%20typically%20found%20on%20newer%20American%20and%20Israeli%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Irbis-E%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20lights%20up%20the%20aircraft%20to%20all%20observers%20in%20the%20neighborhood%26quot%3B%20when%20used%20at%20full%20power%2C%20Roblin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20US%20or%20Israel%20would%20likely%20%26quot%3Bgo%20out%20of%20their%20way%26quot%3B%20to%20destroy%20Iranian%20Su-35s%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20it's%20not%20clear%20if%20Iran%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-targeting-cant-catch-ukraine-air-force-top-us-general-2023-9%5C%22%3Edodge%20those%20strikes%20as%20well%20as%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Su-35%20is%20a%20first%20step%20to%20modernizing%20Iran's%20air%20force%2C%20the%2024%20that%20Tehran%20is%20reportedly%20receiving%20will%20only%20be%20a%20limited%20upgrade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20Iran's%20economic%20circumstances%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20even%20more%204.5-generation%20jets%20would%20likely%20be%20exorbitant%2C%20and%20the%20huge%20sums%20could%20be%20spent%20on%20military%20capabilities%20with%20a%20better-guaranteed%20bang%20for%20the%20buck%2C%20like%20ground-based%20air%20defenses%2C%20drones%2C%20or%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20said.%20%26quot%3BIran's%20air%20force%20and%20its%20tentative%20modernization%20look%20more%20useful%2C%20though%2C%20if%20considered%20as%20a%20defense%20against%20less%20capable%20regional%20enemies%20or%20even%20internal%20uprisings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Csection%20data-track-content%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-post-type%3D%5C%22post%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPaul%20Iddon%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20and%20columnist%20who%20writes%20about%20Middle%20East%20developments%2C%20military%20affairs%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20history.%20His%20articles%20have%20appeared%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20publications%20focused%20on%20the%20region.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-air-force-could-still-have-advantages-without-russian-jets-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703031421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581ada51c5c7b8c9a099f71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-air-force-could-still-have-advantages-without-russian-jets-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iran%20might%20be%20able%20to%20eke%20out%20some%20home-field%20advantages%20depending%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20fight%20it%20faces%2C%20analysts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Paul%20Iddon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-air-force-could-still-have-advantages-without-russian-jets-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20Watch%20ban%20could%20cost%20the%20company%20%24300-%24400%20million%20in%20lost%20sales%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Incoming%20call%20on%20Apple%20Watch%20Series%209%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6500a19e7cfadd001913c468%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20incoming%20call%20on%20Apple%20Watch%20Series%209.%3Cp%3EApple%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20regulators%20ruled%20that%20new%C2%A0Apple%20Watches%20infringe%20upon%20existing%20patents%20held%20by%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EMasimo%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20ruling%2C%20Apple%20said%20it%20would%20stop%20selling%20two%20models%20of%20the%20Apple%20Watch%20this%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20halt%20in%20sales%20could%20cost%20the%20company%20between%20%24300-400%20million%2C%20a%20Wedbush%20analyst%20estimated.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Apple%20moves%20ahead%20with%20its%20tentative%20plan%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-halting-sales-series-9-ultra-2-watch-united-states-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estop%20selling%20two%20of%20the%20latest%20models%20of%20Apple%20Watches%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%2C%20it%20could%20cost%20the%20company%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Apple%20announced%20plans%20to%20stop%20selling%20the%20Series%209%20and%20Ultra%202%20versions%20of%20its%20smartwatch%20for%20US%20customers%20online%20beginning%20Thursday%20afternoon%2C%20and%20in%20its%20stores%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disruption%20will%20likely%20cost%20Apple%20about%20%24300-400%20million%20in%20holiday-season%20sales%2C%20Wedbush%20Securities%20analyst%20Dan%20Ives%20estimated.%20That's%20a%20relative%20drop%20in%20the%20bucket%20for%20Apple%2C%20given%20that%20analysts%20are%20expecting%20Apple%20to%20generate%20nearly%20%24120%20billion%20in%20sales%20during%20the%20October-December%20period%2C%20including%20the%20holiday%20shopping%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sales%20suspension%20on%20the%20two%20Apple%20Watch%20models%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20move%20the%20needle%20much%20for%20the%20company%2C%20but%20still%2C%20it%20couldn't%20have%20come%20at%20a%20worse%20possible%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Ives%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple's%20stock%20so%20far%20hasn't%20been%20significantly%20affected%20by%20the%20announced%20sales%20suspension%20on%20the%20two%20watch%20models%2C%20leaving%20the%20shares%20near%20their%20record%20high%20reached%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApple%20strongly%20disagrees%20with%20the%20order%20and%20is%20pursuing%20a%20range%20of%20legal%20and%20technical%20options%20to%20ensure%20that%20Apple%20Watch%20is%20available%20to%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20representative%20for%20Apple%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BShould%20the%20order%20stand%2C%20Apple%20will%20continue%20to%20take%20all%20measures%20to%20return%20Apple%20Watch%20Series%209%20and%20Apple%20Watch%20Ultra%202%20to%20customers%20in%20the%20US%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EApple's%20patent%20dispute%20has%20reached%20the%20White%20House%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple's%20move%20to%20halt%20sales%20of%20its%20new%20smartwatch%20models%20stems%20from%20an%20October%20decision%20by%20the%20International%20Trade%20Commission%20restricting%20Apple's%20watches%20with%20the%20Blood%20Oxygen%20measurement%20feature%20as%20part%20of%20an%20intellectual%20property%20dispute%20with%20the%20medical%20technology%20company%20Masimo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20had%2060%20days%20to%20review%20the%20ITC%20order%20issued%20on%20October%2026%2C%20meaning%20Apple%20could%20have%20kept%20selling%20the%20two%20affected%20models%20in%20the%20US%20through%20Christmas.%20But%20the%20Cupertino%2C%20California%2C%20company%20said%20in%20a%20Monday%20statement%20that%20it%20is%20pausing%20sales%20early%20to%20ensure%20it%20complies%20with%20the%20ITC%20order%2C%20in%20an%20apparent%20indication%20that%20the%20company%20isn't%20confident%20that%20the%20White%20House%20will%20intervene%20in%20the%20international%20patent%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%20reported%20that%20it's%20unlikely%20the%20Biden%20administration%20will%20overturn%20the%20ruling%2C%20but%20is%20possible%20and%20has%20happened%20before.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fobama-vetoes-ban-on-iphone-and-ipad-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFormer%20President%20Barack%20Obama%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202013%20vetoed%20an%20ITC%20ban%20on%20some%20models%20of%20the%20iPhone%20and%20iPad%20following%20a%20similar%20patent%20dispute%20between%20Apple%20and%20Samsung.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20press%20secretary%20Karine%20Jean-Pierre%20said%20the%20Biden%20administration%20was%20tracking%20the%20Apple%20Watch%20trade%20case.%20She%20said%20US%20Trade%20Representative%20Katherine%20Tai%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20matter%20and%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bcarefully%20considering%20all%20of%20the%20factors%20in%20this%20case.%26quot%3B%20Jean-Pierre%20said%20she%20didn't%20want%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20any%20decision%20Tai%20might%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMore%20patent%20disputes%20may%20be%20on%20the%20horizon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20ITC's%20sales%20ban%20isn't%20overturned%2C%20Apple%20pledged%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20all%20measures%26quot%3B%20to%20resume%20sales%20of%20the%20Series%209%20and%20Ultra%202%20models%20in%20the%20US%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-12-18%2Fapple-plans-rescue-for-17-billion-watch-business-in-face-of-ban%3Fsrnd%3Dpremium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company's%20engineers%20are%20scrambling%20to%20make%20last-minute%20software%20changes%20to%20the%20watches%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20work%20around%20the%20ITC's%20ruling%2C%20though%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20their%20efforts%20will%20prevent%20the%20ban%20from%20taking%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Apple%20Watch%20SE%2C%20which%20lacks%20the%20Blood%20Oxygen%20feature%2C%20will%20remain%20on%20sale%20in%20the%20US%20after%20Christmas%20Eve.%20Previously%20purchased%20Apple%20Watches%20equipped%20with%20the%20Blood%20Oxygen%20feature%20aren't%20affected%20by%20the%20ITC%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20patent%20roadblock%20the%20Apple%20Watch%20has%20run%20into%20as%20it%20increasingly%20morphs%20into%20a%20health-management%20device.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20ITC%20ruled%20that%20Apple%20had%20infringed%20on%20the%20wearable%20EKG%20technology%20of%20AliveCor%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20the%20Biden%20administration%20declined%20to%20overturn.%20That%20dispute%20hasn't%20directly%20affected%20Apple%20Watch%20sales%20yet%20because%20another%20regulatory%20body%20had%20ruled%20that%20AliveCor's%20technology%20isn't%20patentable.%20The%20legal%20tussle%20on%20that%20issue%20is%20still%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20patent%20headaches%20facing%20Apple%20as%20it%20tries%20to%20infuse%20more%20medical%20technology%20into%20its%20watch%20models%20make%20it%20increasingly%20likely%20the%20company%20will%20either%20have%20to%20start%20working%20out%20licensing%20deals%20or%20simply%20acquire%20startups%20specializing%20in%20the%20field%2C%20Ives%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-watch-ban-could-cost-the-company-400-million-sales-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703031137000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658212b8a79e5746976b46c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-watch-ban-could-cost-the-company-400-million-sales-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20a%20regulator's%20ruling%20that%20new%20Apple%20Watches%20infringe%20upon%20patents%20held%20by%