th%20your%20partner%2C%20or%20feel%20stuck%20in%20a%20relationship%20slump%2C%20it's%20normal%20to%20wonder%20if%20your%20dynamic%20is%20still%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20if%20a%20relationship%20is%20past%20the%20point%20of%20saving%2C%20there%20are%20compounding%20factors%20at%20play%2C%20like%20being%20critical%20of%20a%20partner's%20character%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20interest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Frelationship-goals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eimproving%20your%20bond%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Aldrich%20Chan%2C%20a%20therapist%20and%20neuropsychologist.%20If%20one%20or%20both%20partners%20exhibits%20these%20behaviors%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20your%20relationship%20is%20fizzling%20out%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20weathering%20some%20challenging%20periods%20and%20disagreements%20with%20your%20partner%20is%20normal%2C%20and%20can%20certainly%20strengthen%20a%20relationship%20when%20handled%20with%20care%2C%20Chan%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20multiple%20factors%20are%20co-occurring%2C%20or%20occurring%20all%20in%20tandem%2C%20it%20can%20really%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20relationship%20failing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20criticize%20your%20character%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20thing%20to%20feel%20frustration%20or%20annoyance%20towards%20your%20partner%20from%20time%20to%20time.%20But%20if%20you%20or%20your%20partner%20repeatedly%20respond%20to%20those%20negative%20feelings%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbeing-in-a-controlling-relationship-can-affect-your-health-lifespan-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eattacking%20the%20other%20person's%20character%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20could%20irreparably%20harm%20your%20connection%2C%20according%20to%20Chan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20when%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20argue%2C%20the%20conversation%20regularly%20devolves%20into%20hurtful%20remarks%20or%20sarcastic%20retorts%2C%20it%20can%20put%20emotional%20distance%20between%20partners%20or%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-your-partner-resents-you-like-starting-fights-withholding-sex-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20lead%20to%20resentment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20characterized%20by%20a%20demeaning%20attitude%2C%20where%20one%20partner%20acts%20with%20moral%20superiority%20over%20the%20other%20partner%2C%26quot%3B%20Chan%20told%20BI.%20In%20a%20healthy%20dynamic%2C%20partners%20argue%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20understanding%20each%20other%2C%20not%20putting%20one%20another%20down%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20go%20silent%20during%20tough%20moments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20heated%20disagreements%2C%20some%20people%20can%20feel%20overwhelmed%20and%20may%20need%20to%20take%20a%20pause%20to%20process%20their%20emotions%20before%20finding%20a%20solution%20with%20their%20partner.%20It's%20normal%2C%20and%20even%20helpful%2C%20to%20ask%20for%20space%20to%20do%20this%2C%20Chan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20someone%20goes%20quiet%20without%20communicating%20their%20need%20to%20do%20so%20first%2C%20and%20gives%20their%20partner%20the%20silent%20treatment%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20the%20relationship%20isn't%20working%2C%20according%20to%20Chan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20behavior%2C%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fstonewalling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Bstonewalling%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20erode%20trust%20and%20connection%20because%20it%20leaves%20the%20other%20partner%20feeling%20threatened%20and%20uncertain%20during%20a%20major%20point%20of%20tension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20doesn't%20agree%20with%2