ack%20Obama%20or%20George%20W.%20Bush%20can't%20run%20for%20president%20again%2C%20either.%20So%20we%20have%20these%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20that%20are%20designed%20to%20limit%20or%20place%20constraints%20on%20voters%2C%26quot%3B%20Muller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20this%20is%20a%20deeply%20contested%20question.%20Unlike%20dealing%20with%20an%2018-year-old%20or%20Barack%20Obama%2C%20where%20we%20know%20they're%20obviously%20not%20qualified%2C%20this%20is%20a%20contentious%20issue%20fraught%20with%20major%20questions.%20I%20think%20it's%20probably%20an%20instinct%20that%20some%20people%20have%20to%20let%20the%20political%20process%20play%20out%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20the%20law%20says%20you're%20not%20qualified%20to%20serve%2C%20then%20there%20are%20mechanisms%20in%20place%20to%20try%20to%20exclude%20ineligible%20candidates%20from%20the%20ballot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Hillary%20Clinton%20won%20Colorado's%20nine%20electoral%20votes%20with%20a%204.9%25%20margin%20of%20victory.%20Ted%20Cruz%20won%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20delegates%20in%20the%20state's%202016%20Republican%20presidential%20caucuses.%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-presidential-election-2020-live-vote-counts-results-2020%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoe%20Biden%20won%2055%25%20of%20the%20vote%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20margin%20of%2013.50%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20breaking%20story%2C%20please%20check%20back%20for%20updates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-rules-trump-disqualified-from-2024-primary-ballot-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703028546000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65822536cefc010bea254fa3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busi