ttps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580a8e2a79e5746976aa44b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMolten%20salts%20are%20used%20as%20coolants%20in%20the%20Papirus%20installation%20at%20CEA%20Cadarache%20in%20Saint-Paul-les-Durance%2C%20France.%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Tucat%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faircraft-nuclear-propulsion-molten-salt-reactor-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMolten%20salt%20reactors%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20first%20built%20in%20the%201950s%20but%20haven't%20been%20used%20in%20the%20US%20since%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Nuclear%20Regulatory%20Commission%20recently%20issued%20a%20permit%20to%20build%20a%20molten%20salt%20nuclear%20plant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKairos%20Power%20is%20heading%20the%20project%2C%20which%20it%20hopes%20to%20finish%20by%202027.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20issued%20a%20permit%20to%20construct%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20nuclear%20reactor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20a%20molten%20salt%20reactor%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20smaller%2C%20easier-to-build%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20in%20the%20future%20that%20could%20end%20up%20powering%20ships%20and%20other%20off-the-grid%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20reactor%20different%20is%20how%20it%20will%20cool%20its%20core%2C%20using%20molten%20salt%20instead%20of%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWater%20vs.%20salt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Purdue%20University%20Reactor%20Number%20One%20PUR%201%20core%20cherenkov%20radiation%20blue%20glow%20nuclear%20energy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d23691ca17d6c44264942d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Purdue%20University%20Reactor%20Number%20One%20(PUR-1)%20is%20the%20first%20nuclear%20reactor%20in%20the%20US%20with%20all-digital%20controls.%20Here%20its%20core%20glows%20blue%20from%20Cherenkov%20radiation.%3Cp%3EPurdue%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Ftopics%2Fwater-cooled-reactors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eall%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20nuclear%20reactors%20working%20today%20use%20water%20to%20cool%20down.%20Their%20cores%20can%20reach%20temperatures%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fengineering.berkeley.edu%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2Fnuclear-power-renaissance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E572%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20far%20hotter%20than%20water's%20boiling%20point%20of%20212%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20the%20water%20from%20evaporating%20and%20keep%20it%20a%20liquid%20at%20such%20high%20temperatures%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20costs%20additional%20technology%2C%20space%2C%20and%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20salts%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20much%20higher%20boiling%20points%2C%20so%20they%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewouldn't%20require%20the%20same%20expensive%2C%20high-pressure%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20utilize%20it%20at%20these%20high%20temperatures%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20boil%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20V.%20Smith%2C%20project%20director%20of%20the%20molten%20chloride%20reactor%20experiment%20at%20the%20Idaho%20National%20Laboratory%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20have%20big%2C%20thick%20pressure%20vessels%20to%20contain%20coolant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20molten%20salt%20reactor%20tested%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20small%20enough%20to%20fit%20on%20a%20plane%20whereas%20the%20portion%20of%20the%20Diablo%20Canyon%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20in%20California%20that%20generates%20energy%20takes%20up%2012%20acres%20of%20land%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fengineering.berkeley.edu%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2Fnuclear-power-renaissance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBerkeley%20Engineering%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20benefit%2C%20and%20others%2C%20is%20why%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fnuclear-energy-kairos-power-reactor-molten-salt-cop28-f6066bc945d59c5c36a54b1487d37dd9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENuclear%20Regulatory%20Commission%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20issued%20the%20first%20permit%20to%20construct%20a%20non-water-cooled%20nuclear%20plant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20be%20the%20first%20since%201968%2C%20Mike%20Laufer%2C%20Kairos%20Power's%20chief%20executive%20officer%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-12-13%2Fus-approves-new-kind-of-nuclear-reactor-for-first-time-in-50-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKairos%20Power%20is%20the%20company%20that%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20test%20plant%20it%20calls%20Hermes%2C%20which%20will%20be%20cooled%20by%20molten%20fluoride%20salt%20in%20Oak%20Ridge%2C%20Tennessee%20by%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20version%20of%20the%20plant%20won't%20provide%20electricity%2C%20but%20the%20company%20hopes%20its%20successor%2C%20Hermes%202%2C%20will%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Fdocs%2FML2319%2FML23195A125.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2028%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20is%20molten%20salt%20worth%20re-exploring%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Details%20inside%20of%20a%20nuclear%20reactor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582105fa79e5746976b455b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENuclear%20reactors%20could%20get%20smaller%20in%20the%20future.%3Cp%3EXH4D%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMolten%20salt%20reactors%20have%20been%20around%20since%20the%201950s%20but%20the%20US%20mostly%20abandoned%20them%20in%20the%201970s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebulletin.org%2F2022%2F06%2Fmolten-salt-reactors-were-trouble-in-the-1960s-and-they-remain-trouble-today%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20favor%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20water-cooled%20reactors%2C%20many%20of%20which%20had%20already%20been%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20however%2C%20companies%2C%20including%20Kairos%2C%20and%20laboratories%20are%20looking%20into%20salt-cooled%20reactors%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSalt%20as%20a%20coolant%20is%20just%20superior%20to%20water%2C%20once%20you've%20got%20the%20engineering%20details%20hammered%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20molten%20salt%20reactors%20don't%20need%20those%20thick%20pressure%20vessels%20to%20keep%20water%20a%20liquid%20at%20high%20temperatures%2C%20there's%20more%20design%20flexibility%2C%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReactors%20can%20be%20smaller%20than%20water-cooled%20options%20and%20built%20in%20a%20wider%20variety%20of%20locations%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMolten%20salt%20sort%20of%20opens%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20design%20options%20that%20you%20simply%20can't%20get%20to%20without%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20move%20into%20that%20low-pressure%20paradigm%2C%20manufacturing%20just%20gets%20a%20lot%20more%20straightforward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20see%20molten%20salt%20reactors%20as%20being%20prolifically%20deployed%20in%20all%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20from%20remote%20locations%20to%20shipping%20vessels%20to%20large%20power%20plants%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Hermes%20will%20operate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHermes%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworld-nuclear.org%2Finformation-library%2Fcurrent-and-future-generation%2Fmolten-salt-reactors.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoperate%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20temperatures%20up%20to%201%2C200%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%20But%20its%20molten%20salt%20coolant%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20made%20of%20a%20mixture%20of%20lithium%20fluoride%20and%20beryllium%20fluoride%20known%20as%20FLiBe%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fam%2Fpii%2FS0306454917301391%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eboils%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20about%202%2C606%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20well%20above%20the%20reactor%20core's%20temperature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22molten%20salt%20reactor%20experiment%20startup%20glenn%20seaborg%201968%20ornl%2014480987473_11700e3d71_k%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F589da1af6e09a824008b65ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221458%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EManhattan%20Project%20chemist%20Glenn%20Seaborg%20sits%20at%20the%20controls%20of%20the%20Molten%20Salt%20Reactor%20Experiment's%20startup%20with%20uranium-233%20in%201968%20in%20Oak%20Ridge%2C%20Tennessee.%3Cp%3EFrank%20Hoffman%2FOak%20Ridge%20National%20Laboratory%3B%20Flickr%20(public%20domain)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20FLiBe%20will%20remain%20a%20liquid%20at%20those%20high%20temperatures%20without%20additional%20pressure.%20That%20should%20make%20the%20reactors%20easier%20and%20less%20expensive%20to%20build%2C%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKairos%20Power's%20proposed%20fuel%20is%20also%20different%20from%20a%20typical%20nuclear%20reactor.%20The%20company%20plans%20to%20use%20TRISO%2C%20or%20TRi-structural%20ISOtropic%20particle%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20withstand%20extreme%20temperatures%20better%20than%20current%20fuels%2C%20making%20it%20less%20likely%20to%20release%20radioactive%20fission%20products%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fne%2Farticles%2Ftriso-particles-most-robust-nuclear-fuel-earth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUS%20Office%20of%20Nuclear%20Energy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChallenges%20remain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20challenges%20include%20limiting%20corrosion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOxygen%20is%20sort%20of%20the%20driving%20force%20for%20corrosion%20in%20molten%20salt%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20is%20to%20limit%20the%20salt's%20exposure%20to%20oxygen.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20exact%20same%20processes%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20same%20principles%20as%20any%20other%20coolant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20control%20the%20chemistry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMolten%20salt%20reactors%20do%20have%20drawbacks.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bwould%20produce%20several%20different%20waste%20streams%2C%20all%20of%20which%20would%20require%20extensive%20processing%20and%20would%20face%20disposal-related%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20physicist%20M.V.%20Ramana%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebulletin.org%2F2022%2F06%2Fmolten-salt-reactors-were-trouble-in-the-1960s-and-they-remain-trouble-today%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewrote%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2111833119%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20reactors%20could%20produce%20more%20nuclear%20waste%20than%20current%20systems%20and%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bwill%20use%20highly%20corrosive%20and%20pyrophoric%20fuels%20and%20coolants%20that%2C%20following%20irradiation%2C%20will%20become%20highly%20radioactive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmolten-salt-reactor-kairos-power-triso-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703024725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580aa9da79e5746976aa52e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww