aving%20enough%20money%20to%20meet%20all%20of%20their%20basic%20needs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A127%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeless-people-monthly-stipend-california-study-basic-income-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia's%20synthetic%20drug%20use%20is%20skyrocketing%20as%20soldiers%20return%20from%20Ukraine%20with%20addictions%20and%20trafficking%20supply%20routes%20dwindle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20walk%20under%20snowfall%20in%20Moscow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580f8111c5c7b8c9a098922%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoscow%2C%20Russia%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Sefa%20Karacan%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20has%20radically%20altered%20the%20country's%20criminal%20underworld%2C%20a%20new%20report%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussian%20drug%20traffickers%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20find%20new%20routes%20into%20and%20out%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20war%20has%20also%20led%20to%20a%20spike%20in%20synthetic%20amphetamines%20and%20opioids%20in%20Russia%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fallout%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20revived%20a%20period%20of%20criminal%20chaos%20in%20the%20country%20and%20radically%20shifted%20dynamics%20within%20Russia's%20underworld%20drug%20trafficking%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egangs%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%26quot%3BTime%20of%20Troubles%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20December%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalinitiative.net%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FMark-Galeotti-Time-of-troubles-The-Russian-underworld-since-the-Ukraine-invasion-GI-TOC-November-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassessment%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20on%20Russia's%20underworld%2C%20top%20Russia%20watcher%20Mark%20Galeotti%2C%20writing%20for%20the%20Global%20Initiative%20against%20Transnational%20Organized%20Crime%2C%C2%A0reported%20that%20Russia's%20invasion%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20overhaul%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20major%20narcotics%20routes%20once%20used%20by%20Russian%20gangs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%2C%20Russia%20served%20as%20a%20hub%20for%20cross-border%20flows%20of%20all%20types%20of%20illicit%20products%2C%20such%20as%20money%2C%20guns%2C%20drugs%2C%20and%20people%20throughout%20Europe%20and%20beyond.%20Ukraine's%20criminal%20underworld%20once%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20distribution%2C%20Galeotti%20said%20during%20a%20Monday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalinitiative.net%2Fanalysis%2Fthe-russian-underworld-since-the-ukraine-invasion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresentation%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20his%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20Ukrainian%20gangsters%20have%20suddenly%20%26quot%3Brediscovered%20their%20patriotism%2C%26quot%3B%20Galeotti%20said%20during%20the%20presentation%2C%20and%20are%20refusing%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20Russians.%20Ukraine's%20cold%20shoulder%20coupled%20with%20the%20closing%20of%20land%20routes%20in%20countries%20like%20Finland%20have%20forced%20Russian%20gangsters%20to%20find%20alternative%20drug%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20get%20product%20out%20of%20Russia%20and%20into%20other%20parts%20of%20Europe%2C%20traffickers%20are%20increasingly%20turning%20to%20Belarus%20as%20a%20new%20crucial%20transit%20hub%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20border%20controls%20set%20up%20throughout%20Europe%2C%20heroin%2C%20cocaine%2C%20and%20other%20narcotics%20are%20being%20smuggled%20out%20of%20Russia%20via%20Belarus%2C%20Galeotti%20said%2C%20while%20sanctioned%20items%20such%20as%20microchips%20and%20luxury%20goods%20are%20being%20smuggled%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20criminal%20networks%20in%20Russia%20have%20suffered%20under%20the%20new%20dynamics%2C%20Galeotti%20said%2C%20but%20smaller%20gangs%20once%20relegated%20to%20the%20backwaters%20of%20the%20Belarus%20border%20are%20suddenly%20reaping%20in%20the%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20has%20also%20impacted%20demand%20for%20narcotics%20within%20Russia%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20international%20drugs%20such%20as%20cocaine%20and%20heroin%20are%20still%20finding%20their%20way%20into%20the%20country%20from%20countries%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20economic%20pressure%20on%20ordinary%20Russians'%20pocketbooks%20due%20to%20wartime%20sanctions%20has%20changed%20the%20game%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20war%2C%20cocaine%20was%20too%20expensive%20for%20most%20of%20Russian%20society%2C%20while%20the%20use%20of%20heroin%20is%20on%20the%20decline%20throughout%20the%20country%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20affordable%20drugs%20coupled%20with%20unreliable%20trafficking%20routes%20has%20led%20to%20a%20spike%20in%20synthetic%20drugs%20throughout%20Russia%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESynthetic%20opioids%20are%20cheaper%20to%20manufacture%20and%20more%20accessible%20for%20ordinary%20Russians%2C%20Galeotti%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20has%20also%20sped%20up%20the%20use%20of%20synthetic%20amphetamines%20such%20as%20mephedrone%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bsalt%26quot%3B%20in%20Russian%20slang%20%E2%80%94%20because%20of%20increased%20consumption%20in%20cities%20like%20Donetsk%2C%20where%20many%20soldiers%20are%20either%20based%20or%20take%20leave%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Royal%20United%20Service%20Institute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.rusi.org%2F403-SR-R