ack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20massive%20retaliation%20to%20the%20attack%20has%20killed%20thousands%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1737096926917775782%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20(December%2019)%20evening%2C%20Modi%20wrote%20that%20during%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproductive%E2%80%9D%20exchange%20of%20views%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Congoing%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%E2%80%9D%20with%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20two%20had%20%E2%80%9Cshared%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20about%20maritime%20traffic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20disruption%20of%20shipping%20lanes%20after%20Yemen-based%20Houthis%20attacked%20commercial%20vessels%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20to%20protest%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20strikes%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20post%20did%20not%20delve%20into%20specifics%2C%20the%20Israeli%20PM%E2%80%99s%20office%20alleged%20that%20the%20Houthis%E2%80%99%20attacks%20were%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FIsraeliPM%2Fstatus%2F1737100564238840259%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einstigated%20by%20Iran%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20also%20claimed%20that%20Modi%20%E2%80%9Cnoted%20that%20%5Bthe%5D%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20is%20an%20essential%20global%20necessity%20that%20must%20be%20ensured%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20Indian%20PM%20stated%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Chighlighted%20India%E2%80%99s%20consistent%20stand%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20early%20restoration%20of%20peace%20%5Band%5D%20stability%20in%20the%20region%20with%20continued%20humanitarian%20assistance%20for%20the%20affected%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20post%20did%20not%20repeat%20it%2C%20but%20India%20has%20until%20now%20referred%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attack%20as%20an%20act%20of%20terror%20and%20reiterated%20the%20need%20to%20combat%20terrorism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20had%20immediately%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20on%20October%207%2C%20which%20he%20reiterated%20in%20a%20phone%20conversation%20with%20Netanyahu%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20abstained%20from%20the%20first%20resolution%20of%20the%20193-member%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20(UNGA)%20on%20October%2026%20that%20called%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20to%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20its%20language%20did%20not%20refer%20to%20the%20October%207%20attack.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-votes-in-favour-of-unga-resolution-calling-for-immediate-ceasefire-in-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eless%20than%20two%20months%20later%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20India%20voted%20yes%20on%20a%20second%20resolution%20at%20the%20UNGA%20that%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20despite%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20condemnatory%20mention%20of%20Hamas%20in%20the%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20neither%20leader%20referred%20to%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20in%20their%20posts%2C%20Netanyahu%20thanked%20Modi%20for%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20support%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20just%20war%20to%20eliminate%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organization%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Israeli%20PM%20also%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20leaders%20also%20discussed%20advancing%20the%20arrival%20of%20foreign%20workers%20from%20India%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20clarification%20on%20this%20matter%20or%20its%20details%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20Indian%20