%20the%20Wonsan-Kalma%20Coastal%20Tourist%20Zone%2C%20a%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3ENewsweek%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%20The%20country%20hopes%20that%20the%20final%20product%20will%20give%20competition%20to%20Benidorm%2C%20a%20popular%20tourist%20destination%20in%20Spain%20equipped%20with%20beaches%2C%20skyscrapers%20and%20hotels.%20The%20construction%20has%20begun%20for%20the%20sprawling%20complex%2C%20which%20will%20have%20water%20parks%2C%20hotels%20and%20an%20airfield%2C%20the%20outlet%20further%20said.%20The%20resort%20is%20coming%20up%20near%20the%20port%20city%20of%20Wonsan%2C%20and%20one%20of%20Kim%20Jong-Un's%20most%20heavily%20emphasised%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20was%20originally%20scheduled%20for%20completion%20by%202018%2C%20but%20the%20pandemic%20delayed%20construction%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fnorth-korea-tourist-destination-1853434%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3ENewsweek%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMetro%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20that%20the%20thought%20of%20opening%20a%20tourist%20destination%20struck%20North%20Korean%20bureaucrats%20after%20they%20visited%20Spain's%20Costa%20Blanca%2C%20which%20was%20said%20to%20have%20left%20them%20fascinated%20and%20impressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2023%2F12%2F18%2Fwonsan-kalma-kim-jong-un-reboots-building-tourist-beach-resort-19989394%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20outlet%3C%2Fa%3E%20further%20said%20that%2C%20the%20site%20was%20inhabited%20by%20the%20country's%20homeless%20population%2C%20locally%20called%20'kkotjebi'%2C%20in%20February%20this%20year.%20The%20site%20was%20reportedly%20covered%20in%20human%20waste%20and%20soot%20from%20fires%2C%20it%20cited%20a%20report%20from%20North%20Korean%20newspaper%20Daily%20NK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kim%20has%20big%20plans%20for%20the%20Wonsan-Kalma%20Coastal%20Tourist%20Zone%20and%20the%20construction%20could%20be%20completed%20by%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20the%20tourist%20zone%20will%20see%20international%20travellers%20coming%20there%20due%20to%20travel%20bans%20and%20advisories%20over%20security%20threat.%20Before%20Covid-19%2C%20thousands%20of%20tourists%20visited%20North%20Korea%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20of%20them%20from%20China.%20But%20the%20country%20still%20has%20border%20restrictions%20in%20place%2C%20which%20could%20further%20restrict%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20North%20Korean%20government%20continues%20to%20temporarily%20suspend%20all%20passenger%20routes%20into%20and%20out%20of%20North%20Korea.%20The%20British%20Embassy%20in%20Pyongyang%20is%20temporarily%20closed%20due%20to%20these%20restrictions.%20This%20means%20you%20cannot%20get%20consular%20support%20from%20within%20North%20Korea%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20UK's%20Foreign%2C%20Commonwealth%20and%20Development%20Office%20(FCDO)%20said%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702991580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-04%2Fkim-jong-un-parade-afp-650_650x400_81492576992.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnorth-korea-restarts-construction-of-beach-resort-to-woo-tourists-report-4704074%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22North%20Korea%20claims%20that%20the%20Wonsan-Kalma%20Coastal%20Tourist%20Zone%20will%20give%20competition%20to%20Benidorm%2C%20a%20popular%20tourist%20destination%20in%20Spain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnorth-korea-restarts-construction-of-beach-resort-to-woo-tourists-report-4704074%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnorth-korea-restarts-construction-of-beach-resort-to-woo-tourists-report-4704074%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnorth-korea-restarts-construction-of-beach-resort-to-woo-tourists-report-4704074%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Illusory%20or%20Real%3F%20Unpacking%20the%20Recent%20Increase%20in%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fillusory-or-real-unpacking-the-recent-increase-in-womens-labour-force-participation-in-india%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3ECEDA.%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(for%20those%20aged%2015-59)%20has%20seen%20a%20growth%20from%2051.5%25%20to%2058.3%25%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-23.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20growth%20has%20been%20on%20account%20of%20improvement%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20improvement%20in%20the%20initial%20years%20can%20be%20partially%20explained%20by%20a%20change%20in%20measurement.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20sustained%20increase%20reflects%20an%20increase%20in%20women%20in%20self-employment%2C%20which%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20paid%20work%20and%20disguised%20unemployment.%20There%20is%2C%20however%2C%20no%20increase%20in%20job%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Economic%20Forum%E2%80%99s%20Global%20Gender%20Gap%20Report%20for%202022%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fworld%2Fis-saudi-arabia-doing-better-than-india-in-bridging-gender-gap-wef-report-says-yes%2F1036026%2F%5C%22%3Ejaws%20to%20drop%20and%20eyes%20to%20pop%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20put%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20where%20gender%20gaps%20are%20mandated%20by%20law%2C%20ahead%20of%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2022.pdf%5C%22%3Erespective%20rankings%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20gender%20gap%20index.%20In%20the%20following%20year%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2022.pdf%5C%22%3EIndia%20did%20manage%20to%20outrank%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20West%20Asian%20counterpart%20marginally%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20rank%20fairly%20low%20%E2%80%93%20127%20among%20146%20countries.%20The%20index%20measures%20gaps%20on%20four%20broad%20parameters%20(also%20called%20sub-indices)%20%E2%80%93%20economic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%2C%20educational%20attainment%2C%20health%20and%20survival%2C%20and%20political%20empowerment.%20India%E2%80%99s%20poor%20scoring%20on%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%E2%80%9D%20for%20women%20contributed%20substantially%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fgender-gap-report-21-indias-ranking-continues-to-slide%2F%5C%22%3Epersistently%20low%20rank%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20global%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%E2%80%9D%20relates%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20The%20issue%20of%20low%20and%20declining%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(FLFPR)%20in%20India%20has%20been%20extensively%20discussed%20both%20on%20CEDA%20pages%20(see%20examples%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fcovid-19-income-shocks-and-female-employment%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecline-in-female-labour-force-participation-be-cautious-how-you-interpret-it%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fpicture-this-if-indian-states-were-countries-female-lfpr%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%20as%20well%20as%20by%20CEDA%20researchers%2C%20who%20have%20analysed%20some%20key%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X2300253X%5C%22%3Ecauses%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.iza.org%2Fdp14639.pdf%5C%22%3Epatterns%20showing%20that%20women%20work%20when%20work%20is%20available%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iza.org%2Fpublications%2Fdp%2F14497%2Fwords-matter-gender-jobs-and-applicant-behavior%5C%22%3Eremedies%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20rigorous%20empirical%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20data%20from%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Surveys%20(PLFS)%20since%202017-18%20provides%20more%20than%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20as%20it%20reveals%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20overall%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(LFPR)%20by%20the%20current%20weekly%20status%20(or%20CWS%2C%20where%20the%20reference%20period%20is%20one%20week)%20of%20those%20aged%2015-59%20from%2051.5%25%20to%2058.3%25%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-23%20(Figure%201).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20is%20driven%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20FLFPRs%20from%2022.9%25%20to%2034.1%25%20over%20the%20period.%20If%20this%20is%20indeed%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20trend%2C%20it%20is%20undoubtedly%20heartening%20and%20very%20welcome.%20PLFS%20also%20provides%20data%20for%20participation%20rates%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdge.gov.in%2Fdge%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FAnnual_Report_PLFS_2022-23.pdf%5C%22%3Eusual%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20(principal%20and%20subsidiary%20status)%20with%20a%20reference%20period%20of%20one%20year.%20Here%20we%20report%20figures%20from%20CWS%2C%20but%20the%20usual%20status%20trends%20are%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630.png%201152w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630-300x184.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630-1024x628.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689853%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22707%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure1.html%5C%22%3EFigure%201%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrue%20to%20historical%20patterns%2C%20the%20urban%20FLFPR%20continues%20to%20be%20lower%20than%20rural%2C%20but%20both%20show%20an%20increase%3A%205%20percentage%20points%20for%20urban%20and%2014%20percentage%20points%20for%20rural%20women.%20The%20pattern%20of%20increase%20in%20rural%20women%E2%80%99s%20LFPRs%20shows%20two%20big%20spikes%20of%20roughly%206%20percentage%20points%20each%3A%20one%20between%202018-19%20and%202019-20%20and%20the%20second%20between%202021-22%20and%202022-23.%20The%20corresponding%20urban%20increase%20was%20around%202%20percentage%20points%20in%20both%20instances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20useful%20to%20remind%20ourselves%20of%20the%20trends%20in%20LFPRs%20prior%20to%202017-18.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20FLFPR%20declined%20from%2039.7%25%20in%202004-05%20to%2028.9%25%20in%202011-12%2C%20to%20a%20further%2022.9%25%20in%202017-18%20(Figure%202).%20The%20Indian%20government%20started%20using%20the%20PLFS%20only%20in%202017-18.%20Prior%20to%20that%2C%20the%20quinquennial%20Employment-Unemployment%20Surveys%20(EUS)%20were%20used%20to%20measure%20the%20employment%20situation%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20EUS%20was%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20(NSS)%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20(MoSPI)%2C%20the%20same%20ministry%20that%20now%20conducts%20PLFS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631-300x182.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631-1024x622.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689854%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure2.html%5C%22%3EFigure%202%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20increase%20in%20FLFPRs%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20the%20increase%20in%20rural%20women%E2%80%99s%20increased%20participation%2C%20just%20as%20the%20decline%20was%20due%20to%20a%20drop%20in%20rural%20FLFPR.%20Let%20us%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20increase%20using%20the%20same%20set%20of%20arguments%20that%20have%20so%20far%20been%20deployed%20to%20analyse%20the%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20a%20norms%20story%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20historically%20low%20level%20as%20well%20as%20the%20decline%20in%20female%20LFPRs%20have%20been%20widely%20attributed%20to%20conservative%20social%20norms%2C%20both%20by%20academics%20as%20well%20as%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unfpa.org%2Fpublications%2Fmanual-social-norms-and-change-2022%5C%22%3Emultilateral%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20crux%20of%20this%20argument%20is%20that%20women%20are%20not%20allowed%20by%20their%20families%20and%20by%20the%20local%20community%20to%20participate%20in%20paid%20work%2C%20a%20norm%20that%20women%20themselves%20largely%20internalise.%20If%20this%20argument%20is%20true%2C%20the%20latest%20increase%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20FLFPR%20is%20a%20puzzle.%20Did%20norms%20governing%20Indian%20women%20(assuming%20incorrectly%20in%20the%20first%20place%20that%20there%20is%20a%20common%20set%20of%20norms%20applicable%20across%20castes%20and%20communities)%20suddenly%20and%20inexplicably%20loosen%20over%20the%20last%20six%20years%2C%20in%20two%20bouts%3F%20That%20seems%20highly%20unlikely.%20There%20is%20no%20complementary%20evidence%20from%20any%20other%20source%20that%20hints%20at%20this%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20a%20measurement%20story%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20might%20wonder%20about%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20recent%20data%2C%20and%20indeed%20there%20is%20much%20to%20say%20about%20measurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work.%20Does%20the%20recent%20increase%20reflect%20a%20changed%20way%20of%20measuring%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3F%20When%20the%20EUS%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20annual%20PLFS%2C%20there%20were%20some%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20sampling%20design%20and%20interview%20schedules.%20Readers%20interested%20in%20the%20full%20set%20of%20changes%20can%20refer%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdge.gov.in%2Fdge%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-11%2FAnnual_Report_PLFS_2017-18.pdf%5C%22%3Ethis%20document%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20know%2C%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20measure%20both%20participation%20in%20economic%20work%20as%20well%20as%20availability%20for%20economic%20work.%20International%20standards%20count%20economic%20work%20as%20employment%20for%20pay%20or%20profit%3B%20by%20this%20standard%2C%20an%20unpaid%20helper%20would%20not%20be%20counted%20as%20being%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20However%2C%20in%20developing%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20there%20is%20a%20large%20number%20of%20workers%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20who%20are%20involved%20in%20economic%20work%2C%20i.e.%2C%20in%20the%20production%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20that%20get%20counted%20in%20GDP%20but%20are%20not%20paid%20for%20that%20work.%20Women%20in%20unpaid%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eeconomic%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0work%20tend%20to%20fall%20through%20the%20cracks%20of%20the%20statistical%20system%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Fvisible-and-invisible-barriers-women-working-india%5C%22%3Enot%20get%20counted%20as%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20be%20absolutely%20sure%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20among%20the%20new%20features%20of%20PLFS%2C%20two%20might%20have%20contributed%20to%20better%20measurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3A%20one%2C%20for%20each%20day%20of%20the%20reference%20week%2C%20PLFS%20collected%20hours%20worked%20in%20each%20economic%20activity.%20Second%2C%20for%20those%20who%20were%20available%20for%20additional%20economic%20work%20in%20the%20reference%20week%2C%20information%20on%20hours%20available%20for%20each%20day%20of%20the%20reference%20week%20was%20collected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20extent%20this%20is%20a%20measurement%20story%2C%20we%20could%20argue%20that%20the%20earlier%20low%20proportions%20reflected%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X2300253X%5C%22%3Emismeasurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20the%20recent%20increase%20reflects%20improved%20measurement.%20However%2C%20this%20would%20explain%20only%20the%20initial%20increase%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20PLFS%20rounds.%20It%20cannot%20explain%20the%20steady%20increase%20over%20six%20years.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20each%20year%20is%20more%20accurate%20than%20the%20previous%20year.%20Instead%2C%20it%20suggests%20a%20genuine%20increase%20in%20women%20entering%20productive%20work.%20But%20is%20this%20coming%20from%20an%20increase%20in%20jobs%20for%20women%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20about%20more%20jobs%20in%20rural%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20recent%20increase%20in%20FLFPR%20could%20not%20be%20due%20to%20a%20sudden%20increase%20in%20work%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20as%20we%20do%20not%20observe%20any%20corresponding%20spikes%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20of%20rural%20men.%20As%20Figure%203%20shows%20that%20the%20increase%20is%20driven%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20rural%20women%20under%20the%20broad%20category%20of%20%E2%80%9Cself-employed%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20has%20risen%20from%2055.9%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2070.1%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632-300x180.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632-1024x613.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689855%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure3.html%5C%22%3EFigure%203%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20self-employment%20encompass%3F%20In%20brief%2C%20it%20includes%20any%20activity%20where%20one%20is%20not%20working%20for%20an%20employer.%20It%20could%20include%20the%20largest%20entrepreneurs%20as%20well%20as%20a%20farmer%2C%20the%20neighbourhood%20cobbler%20or%20the%20vegetable%20seller%20on%20a%20cart.%20For%20those%20not%20in%20wage%20or%20casual%20work%2C%20participation%20in%20agriculture%20and%20allied%20activities%20counts%20as%20self-employment.%20The%20PLFS%20further%20categorises%20those%20who%20are%20self-employed%20into%20three%20categories%3A%20%E2%80%9Cemployer%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cown-account%20worker%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cunpaid%20helper%E2%80%9D.%20Own-account%20workers%20are%20one-person%20enterprises%20and%20unpaid%20helpers%20typically%20are%20individuals%20working%20on%20family%20enterprises%20but%20not%20being%20paid%20for%20their%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20spike%20in%20FLFPR%20between%202018-19%20and%202019-20%2C%20it%20was%20the%20proportion%20of%20unpaid%20helpers%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ewithin%3C%2Fi%3E%20self-employed%20that%20increased%20(from%2033.1%25%20to%2038.4%25)%2C%20while%20the%20proportions%20of%20self-employed%20that%20were%20own-account%20workers%20declined%20from%2022.9%25%20to%2020.9%25.%20The%20proportion%20of%20rural%20women%20workers%20who%20worked%20as%20regular%20salaried%20workers%20also%20declined%20from%2013.4%25%20to%2010.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20spike%2C%20more%20recently%2C%20between%202021-22%20and%202022-23%2C%20it%20was%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20working%20as%20own-account%20workers%20that%20increased%2C%20whereas%20the%20proportion%20as%20unpaid%20workers%20remained%20stable%20at%20roughly%2038%25.%20Thus%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20female%20LFPRs%20is%20attributable%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20proportions%20of%20women%20working%20as%20own-account%20enterprises%20or%20as%20unpaid%20helpers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20we%20see%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20share%20of%20rural%20women%20working%20as%20casual%20labour%20(from%2031.3%25%20to%2019.6%25)%20and%20no%20change%20in%20the%20proportion%20working%20in%20regular%20wage%20or%20salaried%20jobs%20(roughly%2010%25).%20If%20job%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas%20had%20increased%2C%20we%20would%20have%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20both%20these%20proportions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormally%20a%20shift%20from%20casual%20labour%20to%20regular%20wage%20labour%20signals%20an%20improvement%20in%20work%20conditions.%20However%2C%20Indian%20data%20does%20not%20show%20this%20shift.%20It%20appears%20that%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20as%20casual%20labour%20is%20being%20more%20than%20compensated%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20two%20subsections%20of%20the%20self-employed%20category%3A%20unpaid%20helper%20and%20own%20account%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20disguised%20unemployment%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202017-18%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%20share%20of%20men%20who%20were%20employed%20in%20the%20primary%20sector%20(agriculture%2C%20forestry%20and%20fishing)%20declined%20from%2037%25%20to%2033.4%25.%20However%2C%20for%20women%2C%20this%20share%20went%20up%20from%2052.8%25%20to%2058.8%25%20(Figure%204).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633-300x178.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633-1024x608.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689858%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22713%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure4.html%5C%22%3EFigure%204%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3EMost%20of%20the%20growth%20in%20the%20share%20of%20self-employed%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20of%20those%20working%20as%20own-account%20workers%20has%20also%20been%20in%20this%20sector%20in%20this%20period.%20Figure%205%20shows%20the%20change%20over%20time%20in%20proportion%20of%20men%20and%20women%20across%20broad%20sectors%20and%20by%20type%20of%20employment%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFocusing%20on%20rural%20women%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20who%20are%20self-employed%20in%20agriculture%2C%20from%2063.7%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2079.1%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20roughly%2015%20percentage%20points.%20There%20has%20also%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20self-employed%20rural%20women%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20services%2C%20though%20the%20quantum%20of%20increase%20is%20smaller%3A%2010%20percentage%20points%20for%20manufacturing%2C%20from%2071.7%25%20to%2081.8%25%2C%20and%20six%20percentage%20points%20for%20services%20from%2023.1%25%20to%2029.1%25%20(even%20as%20the%20share%20of%20women%20working%20in%20manufacturing%20has%20only%20increased%20marginally%20while%20those%20working%20in%20services%20has%20seen%20a%20small%20decline).%20Thus%2C%20self-employment%20among%20rural%20women%20has%20occurred%20across%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(