Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure5d.html%5C%22%3E5d%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20increase%20in%20self-employment%20in%20agriculture%20for%20rural%20women%20is%20mirrored%20in%20the%20steady%20decline%20in%20the%20proportion%20working%20as%20casual%20labour%20in%20agriculture%2C%20with%20virtually%20no%20change%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20regular%20salaried%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20the%20decline%20in%20casual%20labour%20been%20reflected%20in%20an%20increase%20in%20regular%20salaried%20jobs%2C%20it%20would%20have%20indicated%20an%20improvement%20in%20job%20quality.%20However%2C%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case.%20The%20increase%20in%20self-employment%20in%20agriculture%20could%20reflect%20disguised%20unemployment%20or%20underemployment%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20too%20many%20workers%20are%20doing%20too%20few%20jobs.%20This%20essentially%20means%20that%20women%20are%20engaged%20in%20agriculture%20but%20not%20to%20their%20full%20productive%20capacity.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20pattern%20of%20earnings%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20self-employed%20women%20earning%20more%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%206%20shows%20gross%20earnings%20in%20constant%20prices%20from%20self-employment%20separately%20for%20four%20quarters%20for%20the%20six%20years%2C%20separately%20for%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20for%20male%20and%20female%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19171952%2Fimage-1638-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19171952%2Fimage-1638-1.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19171952%2Fimage-1638-1-300x186.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19171952%2Fimage-1638-1-1024x633.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689866%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure6a.html%5C%22%3EFigure%206a%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173345%2Fimage-1639-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221182%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173345%2Fimage-1639-1.png%201182w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173345%2Fimage-1639-1-300x188.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173345%2Fimage-1639-1-1024x643.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689871%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure6b.html%5C%22%3EFigure%206b%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20see%20that%20the%20real%20gross%20earnings%20of%20rural%20self-employed%20women%20have%20declined%20over%20the%20six%20years%20for%20each%20quarter.%20For%20the%20April-June%20quarter%2C%20the%20ratio%20of%20their%202022-23%20earnings%20relative%20to%202017-18%20is%20almost%20unchanged%20at%2099.8%25.%20For%20all%20other%20quarters%2C%20we%20see%20a%20clear%20decline.%20The%20ratio%20is%2093%25%20(January-March)%3B%2091%25%20for%20July-September%20and%2089%25%20for%20October-December.%20Thus%2C%20while%20PLFS%20is%20doing%20a%20better%20job%20of%20counting%20economic%20participation%20of%20women%2C%20it%20also%20reveals%20clear%20gaps%20in%20earnings%20of%20the%20self-employed%2C%20the%20category%20of%20women%20that%20is%20driving%20the%20increase%20in%20LFPR%20measurement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20salaried%20work%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20regular%20salaried%20work%20has%20not%20increased%2C%20we%20should%20note%20that%20daily%20wages%20for%20rural%20women%20have%20increased%20in%20real%20terms%20(Figure%207)%2C%20as%20indeed%20they%20have%20for%20urban%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173755%2Fimage-1640.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173755%2Fimage-1640.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173755%2Fimage-1640-300x189.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173755%2Fimage-1640-1024x644.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689873%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22755%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure7a.html%5C%22%3EFigure%207a%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173935%2Fimage-1641.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221192%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173935%2Fimage-1641.png%201192w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173935%2Fimage-1641-300x188.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19173935%2Fimage-1641-1024x642.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689875%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22747%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure7b.html%5C%22%3EFigure%207b%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20has%20been%20accompanied%20by%20some%20improvement%20in%20working%20conditions.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20female%20workers%20with%20no%20job%20contract%3A%20from%2057.8%25%20to%2050.2%25%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20from%2071.72%25%20to%2055.61%25%20in%20urban%20areas%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-23.%20A%20similar%20improvement%20is%20also%20recorded%20for%20rural%20and%20urban%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20regular%20salaried%20work%20with%20no%20social%20security%20benefits%20has%20increased%20from%2054.9%25%20to%2058%25%20in%20the%20rural%20areas%20and%20from%2049.8%25%20to%2051.1%25%20in%20urban%20areas.%20Among%20men%2C%20this%20share%20increased%20from%2051.6%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2059.3%25%20in%202022-23%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20while%20in%20urban%20areas%20it%20increased%20marginally%20from%2046.5%25%20to%2047%25%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20balance%2C%20women%20in%20salaried%20work%20have%20seen%20some%20improvements.%20However%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20salaried%20work%20is%20barely%2020%25%20of%20the%2034%25%20women%20who%20are%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20lessons%20does%20this%20hold%20for%20policy%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20increase%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20regular%20salaried%20paid%20work%20with%20job%20contracts%20and%20social%20security%20benefits.%20This%20would%20be%20the%20most%20important%20step%2C%20albeit%20not%20the%20only%20one%2C%20towards%20women%E2%80%99s%20economic%20empowerment.%20To%20achieve%20this%2C%20rural%20non-farm%20paid%20employment%20opportunities%20would%20need%20to%20be%20expanded.%20Additionally%2C%20barriers%20such%20as%20the%20lack%20of%20decent%2C%20fast%20and%20safe%20transportation%20or%20childcare%20facilities%20would%20need%20to%20be%20alleviated%20so%20that%20women%20are%20able%20to%20access%20work%20within%20commuting%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20job%20availability%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20female%20labour%20improves%2C%20women%20will%20gradually%20start%20to%20enter%20paid%20work%2C%20as%20they%20have%20done%20in%20every%20society%20in%20the%20world.%20This%20will%20finally%20start%20to%20shift%20the%20needle%20on%20the%20norm%20that%20prevents%20women%20from%20accessing%20paid%20work%3A%20that%20women%20are%20predominantly%20responsible%20for%20all%20household%20chores%20(cooking%2C%20gathering%20fuel%2C%20cleaning%2C%20washing%20dishes%2C%20laundry%2C%20house%20maintenance%2C%20childcare%2C%20elderly%20care%20etc.).%20History%20tells%20us%20that%20norms%20are%20sticky.%20To%20accelerate%20the%20change%2C%20public%20messaging%20from%20the%20highest%20quarters%20should%20strongly%20advocate%20the%20message%20of%20gender%20equality%20within%20the%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ashoka.edu.in%2Fprofile%2Fashwini-deshpande%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAshwini%20Deshpande%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20professor%20of%20Economics%20at%20Ashoka%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702990847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A