nciple%20on%20this%20issue%20advises%20us%20that%20cattle%20are%20important%20for%20the%20economy.%20The%20constituent%20assembly%20debates%20are%20filled%20with%20earnest%20Congressmen%20telling%20the%20nation%20that%20one%20reason%20India%20was%20malnourished%20was%20because%20there%20was%20insufficient%20milk%20for%20our%20children.%20And%20to%20reverse%20this%2C%20it%20was%20necessary%20that%20cow%20slaughter%20be%20banned.%20No%20evidence%20was%20given%20from%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20world%20because%20none%20existed.%20In%20one%20of%20its%20early%20manifestoes%2C%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20had%20opposed%20the%20use%20of%20tractors%20because%20that%20would%20mean%20that%20bullocks%20would%20have%20no%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20years%2C%20of%20course.%20India%20is%20now%20a%20milk%20surplus%20nation%20that%20exports%20its%20produce.%20And%20tractors%20have%20long%20eclipsed%20bullocks.%20But%20the%20cattle%20slaughter%20laws%20not%20only%20remain%2C%20but%20have%20been%20tightened.%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2Fwhy-a-muslim-man-in-gujarat-faces-life-in-prison-for-the-crime-of-transporting-cattle-63e5a6f02c804%5C%22%3Epunishment%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20cattle%20slaughter%20is%20now%20life%20imprisonment.%20No%20other%20economic%20crime%20attracts%20this%2C%20but%20we%20have%20accepted%20that%20we%20are%20so%20full%20of%20passion%20that%20we%20cannot%20turn%20back%20from%20this%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20comes%20with%20reversal%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20proof.%20In%202019%2C%20a%20Gujarati%20Muslim%20was%20accused%20of%20slaughtering%20a%20cow%20to%20serve%20beef%20at%20his%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20wedding.%20The%20police%20told%20the%20court%20they%20could%20not%20prove%20that%20this%20had%20happened.%20The%20forensic%20sciences%20laboratory%20said%20the%20same%20thing.%20The%20judge%20sentenced%20the%20man%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%20nonetheless%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20for%20him%20to%20prove%20that%20he%20was%20innocent%20and%20not%20for%20the%20State%20to%20prove%20his%20guilt.%20The%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fprice-of-the-modi-years-book-excerpt%5C%22%3Esuspended%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20sentence%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20%E2%80%9Cjudicial%20discretion%E2%80%9D.%20Perhaps%2C%20the%20court%20was%20embarrassed%20that%20we%20have%20such%20laws%20on%20the%20book%20in%20this%20era.%20But%20the%20interesting%20thing%20is%20that%20you%20could%20rationally%20argue%20both%20sides.%20The%20higher%20court%20was%20right%20to%20overturn%20the%20sentence.%20But%20the%20sentence%20was%20the%20result%20of%20a%20law%20and%20the%20judge%20was%20not%20out%20of%20place%20in%20convicting%20the%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%20saying%20that%20something%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20threat%E2%80%9D%20is%20sufficient%20to%20send%20to%20jail%2C%20possibly%20for%20years%2C%20if%20the%20present%20is%20any%20indication%2C%20a%20group%20of%20youngsters%20making%20a%20point.%20Whose%20security%3F%20What%20threat%3F%20These%20are%20waters%20too%20deep%20for%20us%20to%20venture%20into%20as%20it%20requires%20adults%20to%20consider%20such%20things%20and%20we%20are%20not%20adults.%20In%201919%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20led%20an%20all-India%20strike%20against%20the%20Rowlatt%20Act.%20In%20support%2C%20a%20crowd%20gathered%20in%20Amritsar%20to%20join%20the%20protest%20at%20Jallianwala%20Bagh.%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20governor%20Sir%20Michael%20O%E2%80%99Dwyer%20claimed%20that%20British%20rule%20was%20under%20threat%20and%20responded%20with%20violence%2C%20unleashing%20the%20Gurkha%20and%20Baloch%20Regiments%20on%20the%20civilians%2C%20killing%20over%20300.%20The%20British%20passed%20the%20Rowlatt%20Act%20in%20the%20face%20of%20opposition%20from%20all%20of%20the%20Indian%20members%20of%20the%20Imperial%20Legislative%20Council.%20The%20British%20claimed%20the%20law%20would%20affect%20very%20few%20Indians.%20However%2C%20Gandhi%20called%20it%20an%20%E2%80%9Caffront%20to%20the%20nation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20was%20so%20offensive%20about%20the%20Rowlatt%20Act%20(more%20properly%2C%20the%20Anarchical%20and%20Revolutionary%20Crimes%20Act%2C%201919)%3F%20Why%20were%20Indians%20so%20angered%20by%20it%20that%20they%20were%20holding%20public%20demonstrations%20and%20opposing%20it%20in%20the%20Council%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20legislation%20did%20away%20with%20fundamental%20principles%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20It%20could%20hold%20people%20without%20charge%20or%20trial%20and%20it%20did%20away%20with%20jury%20trials%2C%20in%20favour%20of%20in-camera%20trials%20by%20judges.%20This%20is%20called%20administrative%20detention%2C%20meaning%20the%20jailing%20of%20someone%20without%20a%20crime%20having%20been%20committed%2C%20merely%20on%20the%20suspicion%20that%20they%20will%20commit%20a%20crime%20in%20future.%20That%20anger%20which%20we%20had%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20British%20trampling%20over%20our%20rights%20appears%20to%20have%20vanished%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20oppression%20under%20a%20government%20run%20by%20our%20own%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAPA%2C%20under%20which%20many%20Indians%20have%20been%20charged%20and%20are%20in%20jail%2C%20does%20not%20define%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20(readers%20would%20do%20well%20to%20read%20the%20latest%20version%20of%20it)%20is%20broad%20enough%20to%20name%20vast%20numbers%20of%20Indians%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorists%E2%80%9D%20because%20it%20is%20so%20loosely%20framed.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20opposed%2C%20by%20all%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%2022%2C%20Bhagat%20Singh%20became%20a%20national%20celebrity%20in%20India.%20His%20act%20of%20rebellion%2C%20his%20desire%20to%20not%20cause%20harm%20to%20the%20enemy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20bombs%20were%20only%20whiz-bangs%20that%20produced%20smoke%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20ability%20to%20express%20himself%20clearly%20ensured%20that%20the%20media%20and%20the%20public%20were%20both%20riveted%20by%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20the%20law%20that%20he%20was%20opposing%3F%20Bhagat%20Singh%20threw%20his%20smoke%20bombs%20to%20oppose%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Bill.%20It%20allowed%20the%20government%20to%20jail%20people%20without%20trial.%20Just%20like%20UAPA.%20Bhagat%20Singh%20was%20right%20to%20oppose%20it.%20He%20was%20right%20to%20oppose%20it%20in%20the%20manner%20he%20did.%20We%20call%20him%20a%20martyr%20because%20he%20was%20punished%20for%20doing%20what%20he%20did%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20us.%20We%20call%20the%20young%20people%20who%20did%20exactly%20the%20same%20thing%20and%20for%20the%20same%20reason%20%E2%80%9Cterrorists%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702978255000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhos-a-terrorist-youngsters-who-sprayed-smoke-in-parliament-just-like-bhagat-singh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bhagat%20Singh%20threw%20his%20smoke%20bombs%20to%20oppose%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Bill.%20It%20allowed%20the%20government%20to%20jail%20people%20without%20trial.%20Just%20like%20UAPA%2C%20under%20which%20many%20Indians%20have%20been%20charged%20and%20are%20in%20jail.%20It%20does%20not%20define%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhos-a-terrorist-youngsters-who-sprayed-smoke-in-parliament-just-like-bhagat-singh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20to%20compete%20at%20Eurovision%20despite%20boycott%20threats%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702977960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-israel-eurovision_6397750.jpg%3F2023121